# DFS Traversal Quick Revision Notes

---

# DFS (Depth First Search)

DFS explores a tree by going as deep as possible before backtracking.

**DFS Traversals:**

1. Preorder (Root → Left → Right)
2. Inorder (Left → Root → Right)
3. Postorder (Left → Right → Root)

---

# Visualization

Consider the tree:

```text
        1
       / \
      2   3
     / \
    4   5
```

---

# 1. PREORDER TRAVERSAL

## Order

```text
Root → Left → Right
```

## Output

```text
1 2 4 5 3
```

## Recursive Code

```java
static void preorder(TreeNode root) {
    if(root == null) return;

    System.out.print(root.val + " ");
    preorder(root.left);
    preorder(root.right);
}
```

## Remember

```text
Visit node FIRST
```

or

```text
Print before recursion
```

---

## Used In

### Tree Copy / Clone

Need root before children.

### Serialization

Store parent first.

### Expression Trees

Prefix notation.

Example:

```text
+ A B
```

---

## Interview Trick

```text
Root appears first.
```

If first element matters → Think Preorder.

---

# 2. INORDER TRAVERSAL

## Order

```text
Left → Root → Right
```

## Output

```text
4 2 5 1 3
```

## Recursive Code

```java
static void inorder(TreeNode root) {
    if(root == null) return;

    inorder(root.left);
    System.out.print(root.val + " ");
    inorder(root.right);
}
```

## Remember

```text
Visit node in the MIDDLE
```

or

```text
Print between recursive calls
```

---

## Used In

### Binary Search Tree (BST)

Produces sorted order.

Example:

```text
BST Inorder = Sorted Array
```

---

### Kth Smallest Element

```text
Inorder traversal
```

because elements come sorted.

---

### BST Validation

Check if inorder sequence is sorted.

---

## Interview Trick

Whenever you see:

```text
Sorted order
BST
Kth smallest
```

Think:

```text
INORDER
```

---

# 3. POSTORDER TRAVERSAL

## Order

```text
Left → Right → Root
```

## Output

```text
4 5 2 3 1
```

## Recursive Code

```java
static void postorder(TreeNode root) {
    if(root == null) return;

    postorder(root.left);
    postorder(root.right);
    System.out.print(root.val + " ");
}
```

## Remember

```text
Visit node LAST
```

or

```text
Print after recursion
```

---

## Used In

### Delete Tree

Delete children before parent.

```text
Child → Parent
```

---

### Calculate Tree Height

Need child results first.

---

### Diameter of Tree

Need subtree information first.

---

### Expression Trees

Postfix notation.

Example:

```text
A B +
```

---

## Interview Trick

Whenever question says:

```text
Process children first
Delete tree
Bottom-up
```

Think:

```text
POSTORDER
```

